The paper discusses a security technique for integrated circuits, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves analyzing the structural and functional properties of circuits, which falls under the category of digital circuits (cs.DC). The paper proposes a new attack on logic locking algorithms, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper involves analyzing the resilience of circuits to attacks, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the paper involves evaluating the effectiveness of the proposed attack through experiments, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
